  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Wash your <strong>pak choi</strong>, trim off the roots and discard, then separate the leaves</p><p>Cut pieces of <strong>baking paper </strong>(or tin foil) approx. the size of A3 sheets of paper, then lay the<strong> pak choi leaves </strong>in the middle of 2 pieces of <strong>baking paper </strong>(doubling it up prevents any leakages) and add to a baking tray (or two!)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1601376150921-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1601376150921-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1601376150921-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1601376150921-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1601376150921-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Slice your<strong> red chilli[es] </strong>into rounds</p><p>Tip: Not a fan of spice? Remove the seeds!</p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1601376167577-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1601376167577-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1601376167577-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1601376167577-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1601376167577-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>chopped creamed coconut </strong>in a jug with your <strong>tamari soy sauce</strong>,<strong> ginger & garlic paste, sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 3 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [4 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Mix until fully combined – this is your<strong> fiery coconut sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1601376173266-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1601376173266-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1601376173266-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1601376173266-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1601376173266-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse your <strong>blanched edamame beans</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong></p><p>Sprinkle the <strong>edamame beans</strong> over the pak choi, then top with <strong>half </strong>the<strong> chilli rounds </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1601376185205-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
